{"id":"math120-deriv_power210-001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Derivatives Rules","subtopic":"Power rule","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Use the power rule to find the derivative of f(x) = {a}x^{n}. Then evaluate f'({c_val}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":6},"n":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":4},"c_val":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"deriv_power210","steps":["Power rule: d/dx[{a}x^{n}] = {coeff}x^{new_exp}.","f'({c_val}) = {coeff}({c_val})^{new_exp} = {answer_deriv_power210}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","derivative","power-rule"]}
